Fourth Department,

September, 1940.

(September 20, 1940.) In the Matter of the Judicial Settlement of the Accounts of Frank J. Maguire, as Executor and Trastee under the Last Will and Testament of Josephine V. Blodgett, Deceased.

Order affirmed, without costs of this appeal to any party. All concur, Dowling, J., not voting. (The order specifies certain papers which should constitute a record on appeal.) Present — Crosby, P. J., Cunningham, Dowling, Harris and McCurn, JJ.
